sp_scores.title: Defeat Siren before she becomes undead.

tip_battle.message: Siren assumes her undead form every few turns. Hit her with fire and healing magic while she's undead, kupo! To use healing magic on her, tap her first to target her!
tip_battle.title: Siren

dungeons.epilogue: Bartz's party finds their way through the ghost ship and back to dry land where they encounter the dread Siren. Her illusions ensnare the heroes in visions of the past, but Galuf, having lost his memory, is immune. He awakens the others and they prevail against the Siren. Soon after, they arrive at the port of Carwen.
dungeons.name: Ship Graveyard
dungeons.prologue: Their vessel reaches the Ship Graveyard, a haunt of derelict ships teeming with undead. The party makes its way through a ghost ship in search of a way out.

sp_scores.title: Defeat the Wing Raptor without having any attacks countered.
Defeat the Wing Raptor before it closes its wings.

tip_battle.message: Wing Raptor folds its wings every few turns, kupo. Attack while its wings are folded and it will counterattack with its powerful Claw ability! Be patient and wait until it unfurls its wings before attacking!
tip_battle.title: Wing Raptor

dungeons.epilogue: Upon reaching the Crystal Room, they find the Wind Crystal shattered. A vision of Lenna's father appears, who calls them "The Warriors of Light" and charges them with the preservation of the remaining crystals. From the crystal's fragments, the four assume the power of legendary heroes and make for Walse Tower and the Water Crystal.
dungeons.name: Wind Shrine
dungeons.prologue: Princess Lenna Tycoon goes in search of her father, meeting Bartz, Galuf, and the pirate Faris along the way. Together, they enter the Wind Shrine to obtain the crystal within.

sp_scores.title: Defeat Siren before she becomes undead.

tip_battle.message: Siren assumes her undead form every few turns. Hit her with fire and healing magic while she's undead, kupo! To use healing magic on her, tap her first to target her!
tip_battle.title: Siren

dungeons.epilogue: Bartz's party finds their way through the ghost ship and back to dry land where they encounter the dread Siren. Her illusions ensnare the heroes in visions of the past, but Galuf, having lost his memory, is immune. He awakens the others and they prevail against the Siren. Soon after, they arrive at the port of Carwen.
dungeons.name: Ship Graveyard
dungeons.prologue: Their vessel reaches the Ship Graveyard, a haunt of derelict ships teeming with undead. The party makes its way through a ghost ship in search of a way out.

sp_scores.title: Exploit Shiva's weakness to fire attacks.

tip_battle.message: Shiva and the Ice Commanders are both vulnerable to fire, kupo! Bring spells like Fire to this fight!
tip_battle.title: Shiva

dungeons.epilogue: Lenna pleaded with the king to stop misusing the Water Crystal's power, lest it be destroyed like the Wind Crystal before it. But the king refused, citing the prosperity the Crystal had brought his realm, and insisting his people would never allow it. In the midst of the party's audience with the king, they learned that a meteorite had just fallen near Walse Tower. The king gathered a royal guard and headed to investigate, with Bartz and the others close behind.
dungeons.name: Castle Walse
dungeons.prologue: Having nursed her wind drake to health, Lenna and the others ride the drake to Castle Walse to beg the king not to misuse the power of the Water Crystal.

sp_scores.title: Defeat Iron Claw before he uses Death Claw.

tip_battle.message: Iron Claw's brutal Death Claws ability will leave your HP hanging by a thread, kupo! Come equipped with abilities that can fully heal you, like Curaga and Curaja!
tip_battle.title: Iron Claw

dungeons.epilogue: After meeting Cid in the castle dungeons, Bartz and his party stole onto the fire-powered ship where they restored Queen Karnak to her senses and rushed to reach the Fire Crystal, but too late--a possessed guard had already overloaded the Crystal. Though the party was saved by the werewolf, who seemed to know something of Galuf's past, the Crystal was destroyed. The party set out for clues to help them save the last Crystal.
dungeons.name: Karnak Castle
dungeons.prologue: The party steps through a teleporter in the Walse Meteorite and finds themselves transported to Karnak. There they are mistaken for allies of the werewolf attempting to steal the Fire Crystal, and they are imprisoned in Karnak Castle.

sp_scores.title: Exploit the Sandworm's weakness to water attacks.
Defeat the Sandworm without being KO'd.
Defeat the Sandworm before it uses Gravity.

tip_battle.message: The Sandworm's got some unusual moves that make it a particularly challenging foe, kupo! Attack him when he's in his Holes and he'll hit back with Gravity, so better leave him alone when he's hiding! Area attacks will hit the Holes, too, so be extra careful, kupo! Once he's out in the open, hit him with every water attack you've got!
tip_battle.title: Sandworm

dungeons.epilogue: Bartz’s party tried to make their way across the Desert of the Shifting Sands, but true to their name, the sands proved too treacherous to traverse on foot. If only they could float through the air, as it is said King Tycoon did... They were saved when Cid and Mid came to their rescue, defeating the Sandworm that lived in the desert and using its body as a bridge to cross the dunes.
dungeons.name: Desert of Shifting Sands
dungeons.prologue: While they are at the Library of the Ancients, Bartz’s party learns that the missing King Tycoon has been spotted, and proceed to follow his trail into the Desert of the Shifting Sands.

sp_scores.title: Exploit the Sandworm's weakness to water attacks.

tip_battle.message: The Sandworm's got some unusual moves that make it a particularly challenging foe, kupo! tip_battle.title: Sandworm

sp_scores.title: Exploit the Cray Claw's weakness to lightning attacks.
Defeat the Cray Claw without being KO'd.

tip_battle.message: The Cray Claw's Tail Screw is nothing to laugh at, kupo! One hit will take you down to 1% HP! You'll definitely want to be ready with a Curaga or a Curaja in case you get hit! Oh, and strike back with lightning attacks, kupo! He hates those!
tip_battle.title: Cray Claw

dungeons.epilogue: When Faris met King Tycoon in the ruins and called him “father,” she accepted Lenna as her sister, and the two siblings were reunited. Meanwhile, Bartz’s party discovered an ancient airship, the Catapult, which Cid and Mid restored for them to use as their new transportation.
dungeons.name: Catapult
dungeons.prologue: Beyond the desert, Bartz’s party finds King Tycoon, only to fall into ancient underground ruins, where they discover a device that teleports them to the island of Crescent.

sp_scores.title: Defeat Garula without being KO'd.

tip_battle.message: When the Garula's health is low, it will attack multiple times in a row and counterattack too, kupo! Save your abilities until this final phase, then blast it down!
tip_battle.title: Garula

dungeons.epilogue: Atop the tower, the party encountered a rampaging Garula attempting to destroy the Water Crystal. Though they defeated the Garula, they could not save the Crystal, and the tower began to sink into the ocean. Syldra rushed to save the party, but it took all her strength, and with a final plaintive cry she disappeared beneath the waves.
dungeons.name: Walse Tower
dungeons.prologue: Bartz and his party arrive at Walse Tower, the keeping place of the Water Crystal. The king of Walse asks them to ascend the tower and protect the Crystal.

sp_scores.title: Exploit Shiva's weakness to fire attacks.

tip_battle.message: Shiva and the Ice Commanders are both vulnerable to fire, kupo! Bring spells like Fire to this fight!
tip_battle.title: Shiva

dungeons.name: Castle Walse

sp_scores.title: Exploit Ifrit's weakness to ice attacks.
Exploit Ifrit's weakness to water attacks.

tip_battle.message: Ifrit is vulnerable to ice and water attacks, but fire will heal him, kupo! His High Kick ability can paralyze, and his fire attacks are singe-worthy, so be careful!
tip_battle.title: Ifrit

sp_scores.title: Exploit Byblos's weakness to fire attacks.

tip_battle.message: Byblos absorbs all elements but fire, kupo, so stick with fire and victory will be yours! Legend holds that Byblos and Ifrit share a long history…
tip_battle.title: Byblos

dungeons.epilogue: Oblivious to the chaos, Mid had been researching ways to get the fire-powered ship moving again. Mid talked sense into Cid, who felt responsible for the destruction of the Fire Crystal. Encouraged by his grandson's words, Cid began work to refit the fire-powered ship. As he watched Cid and Mid working together, Galuf remembered why he had come to this world: to prevent the banished warlock Exdeath from rising once again.
dungeons.name: Library of the Ancients
dungeons.prologue: Bartz and the party arrive at the Library of the Ancients in search of clues about the last Crystal, but they soon learn that Cid's grandson, Mid, has gone missing. They head down into the depths of the library to find him.

sp_scores.title: Afflict Magissa with Silence.
Afflict Forza with Sleep.

tip_battle.message: Silence Magissa and you won't have to deal with her magic, kupo! Oh, and when Forza shows up and tries to Tackle you, put him to Sleep!
tip_battle.title: Magissa and Forza

dungeons.epilogue: Bartz's party defeats the bandits Magissa and Forza on North Mountain before they can take the wind drake's horns, only to find that the drake is injured and cannot fly. Lenna pushes her way through poisonous plants to find the medicinal Dragon Grass and brings it back to the drake who is instantly healed and agrees to fly the party to Walse.
dungeons.name: North Mountain
dungeons.prologue: The ferry between Carwen and Walse cannot operate without wind, but accounts of a Wind Drake sighting in town inspire the party to head for North Mountain in hopes of finding an alternate means of transport.

sp_scores.title: Exploit Karlabos's weakness to lightning attacks.

tip_battle.message: Karlabos's Tail Screw will leave a character near death, kupo, so heal up quickly if it hits!
tip_battle.title: Karlabos

dungeons.epilogue: With the weakening of the crystal's power, monsters now infest Torna Canal. Bartz and his allies defeat the massive Karlabo at the loss of the Faris's friend since childhood, the sea creature Syldra. With the Wind Crystal shattered and no wind to fill their sails, or Syldra to tug them along, their ship is at the mercy of the current.
dungeons.name: Torna Canal
dungeons.prologue: In order to reach Walse Tower, Bartz and his allies must navigate the Torna Canal, and for this, they require a key from Zok, the canal gatekeeper.
